Agate is a stone that is used to find pearls. When divers want to locate pearls, they tie an agate to a rope and drop it into the sea. The agate is attracted to a pearl, and the diver can follow the rope to where the pearl lies.

Carbuncle	Stone	When it is held against the sun it resembles a burning coal

Diamond	Stone	If a diamond is kept in a house, demons cannot enter

Fire stones	Stone	Stones that burst into flames when brought close together

